  "prompt": "Where can you buy Lego blocks all in the same color?",
  "response": "Finding large quantities of LEGO bricks in a single color can be done through a few different avenues:\n\n*   **LEGO's Pick a Brick:** This online service allows you to select individual LEGO bricks in various colors and quantities. The selection can vary over time, so availability of specific colors might change.\n\n*   **Bricks & Pieces:** Another section of the LEGO website. This allows you to replace missing pieces of LEGO sets. If your desired piece is available in your desired colour, you can order it from there.\n\n*   **BrickLink:** An online marketplace specifically for LEGO bricks and sets. Individual sellers list bricks in various quantities and colors, often at competitive prices. You can filter by color and part type.\n\n*   **LEGO Stores:** LEGO stores sometimes have a \"Pick-a-Brick\" wall where you can fill a container with bricks. The selection varies by store and may not always have a lot of one color. Call ahead to inquire about the color availability.\n\n*   **Bulk LEGO Resellers:** Some companies specialize in selling bulk LEGO bricks, often in mixed colors. While it might require sorting, this can be a cost-effective option for large projects where a specific color isn't critical.\n\n*   **eBay:** Another online marketplace where you can find individuals selling large quantities of LEGO bricks, sometimes sorted by color.\n\nWhen buying bulk LEGO bricks, consider the following:\n\n*   **Price per brick:** Calculate the cost per brick to compare different options.\n*   **Shipping costs:** Shipping can add significantly to the overall cost, especially for large orders.\n*   **Brick quality:** Check the condition of the bricks, especially when buying used bricks.\n*   **Seller reputation:** Read reviews and ratings of sellers on platforms like BrickLink and eBay.",
